### SMILES Validation Gate — Run First, Always

> [!WARNING]
> Every downstream function assumes valid SMILES. `Chem.MolFromSmiles()` returns `None` silently for invalid inputs, which propagates as `IndexError` or `NaN` loss hours into training. Run this once at ingestion and index everything downstream off the validated list.

```python
from rdkit import Chem
import pandas as pd

def validate_smiles(smiles_list: list) -> tuple:
    valid_indices, invalid_records = [], []
    for i, smi in enumerate(smiles_list):
        mol = Chem.MolFromSmiles(smi)
        if mol is not None:
            valid_indices.append(i)
        else:
            invalid_records.append((i, smi))
    if invalid_records:
        print(f"WARNING: {len(invalid_records)} invalid SMILES dropped:")
        for idx, smi in invalid_records[:5]:
            print(f"  Row {idx}: '{smi[:50]}'")
    print(f"✅ {len(valid_indices)}/{len(smiles_list)} valid SMILES")
    return valid_indices, invalid_records

# Call this ONCE after loading:
df = pd.read_csv('tox21.csv')
valid_idx, _ = validate_smiles(df['smiles'].tolist())
df = df.iloc[valid_idx].reset_index(drop=True)
```

### Dataset Sources

| Source | URL | Notes |
|--------|-----|-------|
| Official Tox21 | https://tripod.nih.gov/tox21/challenge/ | Ground truth |
| DeepChem Loader | `dc.molnet.load_tox21()` | Auto scaffold split |
| OCHEM | https://ochem.eu/alerts/list.do | Structural alert SMARTS |
| ChEMBL | https://www.ebi.ac.uk/chembl/ | Bioisostere validation |
| DrugBank | https://go.drugbank.com/ | Pharmaceutical space check |

### Dataset Facts
- **7,831 compounds**, **12 binary toxicity endpoints**
- **NaN prevalence:** 15–25% per endpoint (use -1 sentinel, mask during loss)
- **Toxic prevalence:** 2.8% (NR-AR-LBD) → 16.9% (SR-MMP) — severe, endpoint-variable imbalance

